//Sarah Lynn Reynolds
//Automatically deletes the history of an object when it is selected. 
//Make changes to an object. Run the script. Select object, history should be removed. 



//Scriptjob acts as a trigger. 
//When the condition is 'true' in this case, the command executes. This is the condition. 
//When an object is selected in the scene the condition is 'true'. "DeleteHistory" is the command that deletes history.
scriptJob -conditionTrue "SomethingSelected" "DeleteHistory delete -ch;";
